title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Full Size  4003TSW 40 TACTICAL 40 cal. 40S&W 2 Mags in S&W Case
postcontent:
The Smith & Wesson 4003TSW was introduced in 2000 as a 28.5 oz. lightweight alternative to the ever popular all stainless steel 2.5 lb. 4006TSW. It featues the same 4" stainless steel barrel, stainless steel slide, 11 round .40 cal. 40S&W double stack magazine, and Novak Lo-Mount 3 white dot sights except the chassis is hi-tech aluminum alloy. It was a big hit with law enforcement and this is a former duty pistol manufactured 9/23/2002. As you can see the finish is good even though there are a few signs of holster wear on the right side, normal for a duty pistol which is carried a lot and shot little. The grips are like new and the internals are spotless showing little wear. The laser engraving and accessory rail are often worn on these but excellent on this pistol. The TSW (Tactical Support Weapon) features thicker full length frame rails for enhanced accuracy and delayed unlocking to reduce felt recoil. Even though the 40 S&W round is known for snappy recoil, I found this pistol to be a highly controllable soft shooter for accurate follow up shots and comfortable fun at the range.  The .40 S&W cartridge was developed by Winchester and Smith & Wesson in an effort to to create a round with knock down power similar to the FBI 10mm round (also .40 cal.) but with a shorter case which would facilitate accuracy and allow use of a smaller, more comfortable grip frame. As a result the .40 S&W became the cartridge of choice for law enforcement agencies.The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short, crisp, and light trigger pull on subsequent shots. An ambidextrous safety / decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety.This pistol is extremely CLEAN, well maintained, and scarce in this condition. It comes with 2 S&W factory 11 round magazines in excellent condition in a Smith & Wesson plastic case including an instruction manual, gun lock, wax wrap and paperwork it came with new.
Please email  or call / text Bill 813 . 857 . 8287 for more info or pictures. I'm willing to meet anywhere in the bay area to show this fine pistol.
